COMMON PROGRAMME TWO : EXPERIMENT DESCRIPTION FILE
***************************************************

FILE NAME : CP-2-C:DESC          VERSION 1985-02-18

CP-2-C IS THE MODIFIED VERSION OF CP-M2-D
TO REDUCE TRANSITION EFFECTS AT REMOTE SITES
BY SAMPLING ONLY 320 US OF THE 360 US TRANSMITTED PULSE.
REF. HEIGHT IS 312 KM INSTEAD OF 300 KM TO HAVE THE COMMON VOLUME
MATCHED TO A SIGNAL GATE AT TROMS0 FOR POSITON 4.
OFFSET-PPD = -279
    
THE EXPERIMENT STILL CONSISTS OF A 60 US PULSE TO PROVIDE A
POWER PROFILE WITH A HEIGHT RESOLUTION OF 9 KM,A 360 US
PULSE TO PROVIDE PROFILES OF NE, TE, TI AND VP WITH 54 KM
HEIGHT RESOLUTION AND TO PROVIDE VALUES OF TE, TI, VN AND VE
USING THE MEASUREMENTS AT THE REMOTE SITES , A SECOND 360 US
PULSE FOR REMOTE TO IMPROVE STATISTICS , AND A 20 US PULSE (3KM)
TO ADD A HIGH RESOLUTION POWER PROFILE IN THE D/E-REGION IN TROMS0.
THE PULSE REPETITION TIME IS 8MS.

THE TROMSO BEAM SCANS IN 4 OBSERVING POSITIONS AT 312. KM ABOVE THE
GEOGRAPHICAL POINTS 69.58N-19.21E(VERTICAL), 68.4N-20.0E, 68.64N-21.92E,
(WHERE THE TWO LAST POSITIONS ARE ON A COMMON L-SHELL) AND AT THE
FOURTH POSITION ,68.94N,19.22E  THE TROMSO BEAM IS PARALLELL TO THE 
MAGNETIC FIELD LINE AT 312. KM (AS PREDICTED BY THE IGS75 MODEL FOR 
APRIL 1982). THE CYCLE TIME IS STILL 6 MIN, AND THE ANTENNAS STAY
1.5 MIN AT EACH POSITION.

THE CORRELATOR PROGRAM USED IS PROG7-POW-SI WHICH GIVES THE XX, YY AND XY
COMPONENTS OF THE ZERO LAG SEPARATELY. THIS EXTRA DATA CAN BE USED
TO CALIBRATE THE QUADRATURE DETECTOR AND THE DC AMPLIFIERS.
THE FILTERS USED ARE 25 KHZ BUTTERWORTH FOR ACF IN TROMSO AND
25 KHZ BUTTERWORTH  FOR TROMSO PP1 ,25 KHZ LIN. FOR PP2
AND 25KHZ LINEAR FOR THE REMOTE STATIONS.


TROMSO
******

THE 60 US PULSE IS TRANSMITTED AT F0 (929.5 MHZ), IS RECEIVED ON
CHANNEL 3, SAMPLED AT ADC 3 AND GIVES A POWER PROFILE AT INTERVALS
OF 1.5 KM.

THE 20 US PULSE IS TRANSMITTED AT F2 (930.5MHZ), IS RECEIVED ON CH 5
, SAMPLED AT ADC5 AND GIVES A POWER PROFILE AT INTERVALS OF 1.5 KM.

THE 360 US PULSE1 IS TRANSMITTED AT F3(931.0 MHZ) AND IS ONLY RECEIVED 
AT REMOTE STATIONS.
 
THE 360 US PULSE2 IS TRANSMITTED AT F1  (930.0 MHZ), IS RECEIVED
ON CH4(ALSO AT REMOTE), SAMPLED AT ADC4 AND GIVES ACF'S AT 23 
DIFFERENT RANGES AT INTERVALS OF 27.0 KM.

