KIRUNA AND SODANKYLA
********************

  REMOTE STATIONS ARE FIXED TO OBSERVE AT A HEIGHT OF 312 KM
  IN EACH OF THE 4 POSITIONS.

THE PPD-OFFSET IS USED SO THAT EACH OF THE TWO ACF'S ARE BRACKETED
BY 2 OTHER GATES WHICH NORMALLY WILL CONTAIN A SMALL "SPILL-OVER"
SIGNAL. IF THERE IS A SMALL AND EQUAL SPILL-OVER IN EACH OF THESE
GATES THEN THE TIMING IS CORRECT AND THE SIGNAL GATE IS ADEQUATELY
FILLED SO THAT THE DIFFERENT LAGS IN THE SIGNAL ARE CORRECTLY
WEIGHTED. THIS HAS TO BE CHECKED BY DISPLAYING THE "POWER PROFILE"
AT THE REMOTE SITES. THE "POWER PROFILE" WILL COVER THE 96 FIRST
POSITIONS IN THE RESULT MEMORY.

IN SETTING THE PPD-OFFSET, AN ALLOWANCE IS MADE FOR THE 21 US
DELAY IN THE RECEIVER. IF THERE IS AN ASYMMETRY IN THE SPILL-OVER
GATES THIS CAN BE CORRECTED BY THE OPERATOR, USING THE EROS
COMMAND "OFFSET-PPD".

THE REMOTE ACFS ARE CALCULATED FOR 32 LAGS ONLY.
THE THREE SIGNAL GATES(2 SPILLOVER GATES) FOR BOTH PULSES ARE FOLLOWED
BY 5 BACKGROUND GATES AND 1 CALIBRATION GATE. THE SIGNAL SHOULD BE 
CENTERED IN THE 2'ND GATE SIGNAL1 AND IN THE 11'TH GATE FOR SIGNAL2.

THE POLARISER SETTINGS AT THE REMOTE STATIONS ARE SET TO THE SETTING 
FOR POSITION 4 CALCULATED FROM THE GEOM-PROGRAM OF PHIL WILLIAMS. 

TRANSMITTED FROM TROMSO.

THE CORRELATOR PROGRAM PROG7-POW-SI IS USED AT THE REMOTE STATIONS : HERE
THE "POWER PROFILE" IS, IN FACT, THE 96 SAMPLES  IN THE 3 SIG GATES
AND THIS DATA MAY BE DISREGARDED IN ANALYSIS. BUT THE DATA SHOULD BE
USED TO DETERMINE THAT THE PPD IS CORRECT.

